description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Urology Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General &amp; Specialist Surgery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you dynamic, methodical, hardworking, organised, looking for a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The General &amp; Specialist Surgery Directorate are looking for a highly enthusiastic individual with NHS Medical Secretary Experience, who can work as part of a team as well using their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is to provide a comprehensive, confidential secretarial and administrative support service to one of our extremely busy Urology Consultant Surgeons, to enable them to carry out their duties in an effective and efficient manner and ensure efficiency in patient care.In addition the post holder will provide cross cover for the secretaries during periods of staff absence within the Directorate as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need previous medical secretary experience, outstanding organisational and communication skills; work well with staff and the public, and must be able to demonstrate experience of working under pressure and to set deadlines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, to ensure alignment with the Direct Clinical Care time of the Clinicians for whom they support, flexibility from the core hours may be required and will be determined locally depending upon the needs of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, the post holder will provide cross cover for other secretaries during periods of staff absence within the Directorate, as and when requested.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For specifics please see the generic job description and person spec.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Liz Shaw, Job title: Team Leader, Email address: liz.shaw@ngh.nhs.uk Telephone number: 01604 545604&lt;/p&gt;
